{
  "stem": "7069.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my brother and I soon joined a huge choir that was in process, in progress of practicing for the, for, for, for the oratoria, oratory Handel's 'Creation,' which was performed twice eventually.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, then the next performance, we, we started to rehearse for Mendelssohn's 'Elijah.'",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, this is a very, very odd thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mendelssohn, according to the racial laws of Nuremberg, was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And any where else on German-controlled soil, nothing was allowed to be performed that was written or created by Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And now here, he allowed us to, the commander allowed us to perform 'Elijah,' which couldn't be performed any where else on German soil.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now Mendelssohn, even though he was eventually-- had converted to Catholicism, but based on the Nuremberg laws, he was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so after we performed the 'Elijah'-- until this time, we didn't know that anything was secretly filmed-- it was announced that we should have another performance of the 'Elijah.' And it turns out that it was only for the reason that, in case this one didn't turn out very well, that they have another one.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the second one never took place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because, a few days later, about 50-- at least 50% of the musicians and the performers, singers, we found each other down by the train station to be loaded up to sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my mother at this time was in, in the same camp, living in a little bit different, a little bit away from where we lived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it was basically in the same premises.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Famous people that I met there were-- to us, famous people-- one of the was the impressive person was the, the man who was, at those days, the chief rabbi of Germany, Doctor Leo Baeck-- Rabbi Leo Baeck.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
